Compute band indices

Based on the plot of the raw scans (see convolve_sample_scans script), the radio of red green, and red infrared appear proportional to algae abundance. Normalizing allows for comparability between images of different light intensity, since the ratio is all that matters. RGND was used by Ganey et al, and NDVI is a classic proxy for chlorophyll.

Given the data, feature engineering or multivariate regression to minimize the error is probably not worth it because the measurements have high error and our data is small.

nd <- function(a,b){ (a-b)/(a+b) } # normalized difference function

compute_nds <- function(data, blue, green, red, nir, swir){
  blue <- enquo(blue)
  green <- enquo(green)
  red <- enquo(red)
  nir <- enquo(nir)
  swir <- enquo(swir)
  
  data %>% 
    mutate(ndvi = nd(!!nir, !!red),
           rgnd = nd(!!red, !!green),
           gbnd = nd(!!green, !!blue),
           rbnd = nd(!!red, !!blue),
           ndsi = nd(!!red, !!swir)) %>% 
    select(scan_id, sample_id, ndvi, rgnd, gbnd, ndsi)
}

as_s2_nd <- as_s2 %>% compute_nds(blue = b2, green = b3, red = b4, nir = b8, swir = b11)
as_l8_nd <- as_l8 %>% compute_nds(blue = band_2, green = band_3, red = band_4, nir = band_5, swir = band_6)
as_terra_nd <- as_terra %>% compute_nds(blue = RSR_469, green = RSR_555, red = RSR_645, nir = RSR_859, swir = RSR_1640)

my_plot <- function(df, y, x, title){
  y <- enquo(y)
  x <- enquo(x)
  df %>% 
    ggplot(aes(y = !!y, x = !!x)) +
    geom_smooth(method = "lm", linetype = "dashed", se=FALSE) + #, formula = y~poly(x, 2)
    geom_point() +
    geom_text(aes(label = sample_id), alpha = 0.5) +
    ggtitle(title) 
}

my_plot_crossbars <- function(dat, y_mean, y_sd, x_mean, x_sd, tag){
  x_mean <- enquo(x_mean)
  x_sd <- enquo(x_sd)
  y_mean <- enquo(y_mean)
  y_sd <- enquo(y_sd)

  dat %>% 
    ggplot(aes(y = !!y_mean, x = !!x_mean)) + 
    geom_pointrange(aes(ymin = !!y_mean - !!y_sd, 
                        ymax = !!y_mean + !!y_sd),
                    alpha = 0.4) +
    geom_linerange(aes(xmin = !!x_mean - !!x_sd,
                       xmax = !!x_mean + !!x_sd),
                    alpha = 0.4) +
    theme_minimal() +
    labs(tag = tag)
}

get_formula <- function(mod){
  call <- mod$call %>% as.character()
  call[2]
}

tidy(area_mod) %>% add_column(formula = get_formula(area_mod), .before=1)

make_entry <- function(mod){
  tidy(mod) %>% 
    add_column(formula = get_formula(mod), .before=1)
}

  make_entry(area_mod),
  make_entry(toc_mod),
  make_entry(nitrogen_mod),
  make_entry(albedo_rgnd_mod),
  make_entry(albedo_area_mod),
  make_entry(albedo_carbon_mod)
)
